# AgentAuth — Alembic Migrations

This directory contains database migrations for AgentAuth, managed by Alembic with an async
SQLAlchemy setup (asyncpg driver).

## How it works

- `env.py` loads `DATABASE_URL` from `agentauth.config.settings` (reads `.env` automatically).
- All ORM models are imported in `env.py` so that `--autogenerate` detects schema changes.
- Migrations run in async mode via `asyncio.run()`.

## Common commands

```bash
# Apply all pending migrations
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Roll back the last migration
uv run alembic downgrade -1

# Show current revision
uv run alembic current

# Show migration history
uv run alembic history --verbose

# Generate a new migration from model changes
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe_change_here"
```

## Naming convention

Migration files follow the pattern `NNNN_verb_noun.py` (e.g. `0002_add_delegation_table.py`).
Every migration **must** include a working `downgrade()` function.